entry.content:
Khouribga is considered the most important phosphate production area in the world. Office chÃ©rifien des Phosphates (OCP), the first public company in Morocco manages the mining area. The Province of Khouribga has a large phosphate reserve estimated 35 to 40 billion cubic meters, which has been mined since the 1920s and is ranked first at the international level.
